    // Thread 1: Welcome thread (5 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "AXIOM"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      body:
        '''
        Welcome, all.

        This board has been running in one form or another since 1994.
        The hardware has changed. The software has changed. But the spirit
        remains the same.

        Post freely. Explore the system. Respect each other.

        The SysOp is always watching.

        — AXIOM
        '''
      daysAgo: 540
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "AXIOM"
      subject: "Re: Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      replyToSubject: "Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      body:
        '''
        Good to see the board back online. I remember the last incarnation —
        the one running on Telegard. That must have been, what, 2005?

        Different software now. Different feel. But the name is the same.
        And so is the SysOp, apparently.

        Glad to be here, AXIOM. As always.
        '''
      daysAgo: 538
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NIGHTOWL"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      replyToSubject: "Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      body:
        '''
        Found this board through a link on a retro computing forum. Can't
        believe places like this still exist.

        The terminal UI is gorgeous. Feels like stepping back in time.
        Looking forward to being part of this community.
        '''
      daysAgo: 420
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      replyToSubject: "Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      body:
        '''
        Love the retro vibe here. I've been looking for an active BBS for
        months. Most of them are ghost towns these days.

        This one feels... alive. Something about it.
        '''
      daysAgo: 350
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NEON_PULSE"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      replyToSubject: "Welcome to The Neon Underground"
      body:
        '''
        Bin gerade erst dazugestossen — ich meine, just joined! Sorry,
        English is not always my first instinct when I'm excited.

        This board is beautiful. The colors, the menus, everything. Feels
        like discovering a secret room in the internet.
        '''
      daysAgo: 280
    }

    // Thread 2: System logs (PHANTOM_X investigation, 6 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "PHANTOM_X"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        I was poking around the terminal and noticed some odd entries in the
        system log. Timestamps that don't match up. Activity on nodes when
        nobody was connected.

        Probably just a glitch, but it gave me a weird feeling.

        Anyone else seen anything like this?
        '''
      daysAgo: 210
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "PHANTOM_X"
      subject: "Re: Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      replyToSubject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        What do you mean? I've been on this board for years and never noticed
        anything strange in the logs. Then again, I don't usually go digging
        around in system directories.

        What exactly did you see?
        '''
      daysAgo: 209
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "PHANTOM_X"
      toName: "DARK_MATTER"
      subject: "Re: Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      replyToSubject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        Activity entries at 2am, 3am, 4am. Node 0 showing active sessions
        but the caller log doesn't show anyone connected at those times.
        Repeated patterns, like clockwork. Every Friday.

        Could be automated maintenance, I guess. But the entries are tagged
        as interactive sessions, not batch jobs.
        '''
      daysAgo: 208
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NIGHTOWL"
      toName: "PHANTOM_X"
      subject: "Re: Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      replyToSubject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        I'm on late most nights and I've noticed the board goes into a kind
        of... maintenance mode on Friday nights. Connection drops around
        midnight. Comes back around 3am.

        AXIOM posted about scheduled maintenance. That's probably all it is.
        '''
      daysAgo: 207
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "PHANTOM_X"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      replyToSubject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        Yeah, I saw the maintenance announcement. That explains the downtime.

        But it doesn't explain the sessions I'm seeing *during* the
        maintenance window. Something is happening on those Friday nights
        that isn't just backups.

        I found files in a directory I don't think I was supposed to see.
        Going to dig a little deeper.
        '''
      daysAgo: 195
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "PHANTOM_X"
      toName: "DARK_MATTER"
      subject: "Re: Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      replyToSubject: "Has anyone noticed the system logs?"
      body:
        '''
        Nevermind, forget it. I went back to check and the entries
        I saw before are gone now. The directory too. Maybe I misread
        something. Maybe I was tired.

        Forget I said anything.
        '''
      daysAgo: 190
    }

    // Thread 3: Late night sessions (5 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NEON_PULSE"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Late night sessions are the best"
      body:
        '''
        There's something about connecting to a BBS at 2am that just hits
        different. The quiet, the glow of the terminal, the slow scroll of
        text. It's meditative.

        In Berlin it's already morning when the US crowd is logging on at
        night. Different timezone, different vibe. Who else is a night owl?
        '''
      daysAgo: 145
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "CIRCUIT_JANE"
      toName: "NEON_PULSE"
      subject: "Re: Late night sessions are the best"
      replyToSubject: "Late night sessions are the best"
      body:
        '''
        Agreed. Something about 2am on a BBS feels like you're the last
        person on earth. Just you and the machine.

        I swear the board responds faster at night too. Less load, maybe.
        Or maybe it just *wants* you to stay longer.
        '''
      daysAgo: 143
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NIGHTOWL"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Late night sessions are the best"
      replyToSubject: "Late night sessions are the best"
      body:
        '''
        The board feels different at night. I can't explain it exactly.
        During the day it's just a BBS. But late at night, it feels like
        something else entirely. Like the walls are thinner somehow.

        ...I need more coffee.
        '''
      daysAgo: 141
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "VOID_WALKER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Late night sessions are the best"
      replyToSubject: "Late night sessions are the best"
      body:
        '''
        Night is when the masks come off. During the day we perform for
        each other. At night we're honest.

        I only post at night. Draw your own conclusions.
        '''
      daysAgo: 139
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Late night sessions are the best"
      replyToSubject: "Late night sessions are the best"
      body:
        '''
        VOID_WALKER, that's very philosophical for a Tuesday.

        But yeah, I get it. There's a reason the best BBS sessions always
        happened after midnight. Something about the quiet hours. The glow.

        My wife thinks I'm insane for staying up to use a BBS in 2026.
        She's probably right.
        '''
      daysAgo: 138
    }

    // Thread 4: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X? (6 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        Haven't seen PHANTOM_X on the board in months. Their last posts
        were kind of weird — talking about system logs and strange activity.
        Then they just said "forget it" and vanished.

        Anyone know if they're okay? Did they just move on to another board?
        '''
      daysAgo: 150
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      subject: "Re: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      replyToSubject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        Not in months. Probably just moved on. People drift in and out of
        BBSes all the time. It's the nature of the scene.

        I wouldn't read too much into their last posts. Some people just
        like to be dramatic.
        '''
      daysAgo: 149
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "VOID_WALKER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      replyToSubject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        People come and go. That's BBSes. That's life.

        No point in getting attached to handles on a screen. We're all just
        text in a terminal window. When the cursor stops blinking, does it
        matter why?
        '''
      daysAgo: 147
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NIGHTOWL"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      replyToSubject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        I talked to PHANTOM_X a few times. They seemed genuinely spooked
        about whatever they found in those logs. Then that last post where
        they suddenly said "forget it" — that didn't sound like them at all.

        Probably nothing. But it bugs me.
        '''
      daysAgo: 146
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "CIRCUIT_JANE"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      replyToSubject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        I barely knew them, but the pattern is familiar. People dig into
        things they shouldn't, get paranoid, burn out, leave. Happens on
        every BBS I've been on.

        Not everything is a conspiracy. Sometimes people just lose interest.
        '''
      daysAgo: 145
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      replyToSubject: "Anyone heard from PHANTOM_X?"
      body:
        '''
        I've seen boards go dark before. I've seen users disappear. It
        happens. This one feels different though. Can't put my finger on why.

        But CIRCUIT_JANE is right. No point in conspiracy theories. They
        moved on. End of story.
        '''
      daysAgo: 143
    }

    // Thread 5: MERCURY_R arrives (4 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "MERCURY_R"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "First time here, looks cool"
      body:
        '''
        Hey everyone! Just found this place through a friend of a friend.
        The aesthetic is incredible — feels like I traveled back to 1994.

        Any tips for a newbie? What should I check out first?
        '''
      daysAgo: 105
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      toName: "MERCURY_R"
      subject: "Re: First time here, looks cool"
      replyToSubject: "First time here, looks cool"
      body:
        '''
        Welcome aboard! Check out the message areas — retro.hardware and
        retro.bbs are my favorites. The one-liners wall is fun too.

        And poke around the door games if the SysOp has any running. This
        place has a lot of corners to explore.
        '''
      daysAgo: 104
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "MERCURY_R"
      toName: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      subject: "Re: First time here, looks cool"
      replyToSubject: "First time here, looks cool"
      body:
        '''
        Thanks! I've been reading through the old messages and this
        community seems great. Really active for a BBS.

        Quick question — how long has this board been running? AXIOM's
        welcome says 1994 but some of the messages don't go back that far.
        Was there a wipe at some point?
        '''
      daysAgo: 102
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "MERCURY_R"
      subject: "Re: First time here, looks cool"
      replyToSubject: "First time here, looks cool"
      body:
        '''
        The board has been through several incarnations. Different hardware,
        different software, different eras. But AXIOM has been the constant
        through all of them. At least, that's the handle that's always there.

        Whether it's been the same person all along... well, who can say?
        Welcome to The Neon Underground. Stick around.
        '''
      daysAgo: 101
    }

    // Thread 6: Maintenance windows (5 messages)
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NIGHTOWL"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      body:
        '''
        So every Friday night the board goes down from midnight to 3am.
        That's prime BBS time for us night owls. Can't AXIOM do the
        maintenance on a Tuesday morning or something?

        Three hours seems like a long time for "routine backups" too.
        What's even being backed up that takes three hours?
        '''
      daysAgo: 160
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "BYTE_RUNNER"
      toName: "NIGHTOWL"
      subject: "Re: Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      replyToSubject: "Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      body:
        '''
        Yeah, it's a bummer. I tried connecting during the window once just
        to see what happens and my SSH client just hung. No response at all,
        not even a refused connection. Like the machine wasn't even there.

        Weird. Usually when a service is down you get a connection refused.
        This was just... nothing. Like a black hole.
        '''
      daysAgo: 158
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "CIRCUIT_JANE"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      replyToSubject: "Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      body:
        '''
        Three hours for backups on a BBS this size? That's absurd. The
        entire database can't be more than a few hundred megs. You could
        back it up in seconds.

        I've run BBS software before. Maintenance means rebooting the
        service and maybe rotating logs. Ten minutes, tops.

        Whatever AXIOM is doing for three hours, it isn't backups.
        '''
      daysAgo: 156
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "DARK_MATTER"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      replyToSubject: "Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      body:
        '''
        The SysOp does what the SysOp does. I've learned not to question it.

        Some of you haven't been around long enough to remember what happens
        when you push back on AXIOM's decisions. Trust me — just let it be.
        '''
      daysAgo: 155
    }
    {
      areaTag: "local.general"
      fromHandle: "NEON_PULSE"
      toName: "All"
      subject: "Re: Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      replyToSubject: "Friday night maintenance — anyone else annoyed?"
      body:
        '''
        In Berlin it's Saturday morning during the maintenance window, so
        it doesn't affect me much. But I did notice something odd.

        Last Friday I left a message queued up right before midnight. When
        I came back Saturday, the message was there but the timestamp was
        wrong. Off by about 47 minutes. Like time hiccupped.

        Vermutlich ein Zeitzonenproblem. Probably just a timezone bug.
        '''
      daysAgo: 153
    }

