        '''
        An Apple IIe for pocket change. That's the kind of find that makes
        this hobby worth it. Check those floppies — you might have some
        rare software on them.

        Also, don't overlook the VIC-20s. The VIC was Commodore's first
        real home computer. The sound chip is different from the SID but
        has its own character. People are doing interesting things with
        VIC-20 music these days.
        '''
      daysAgo: 38
    }
    {
